                    "body": "[~rdub]\u00a0The linker error probably is rooted in Homebrew's {{apache-arrow}}\u00a0[dependency on Python 3.9|https://formulae.brew.sh/formula/apache-arrow].\r\n\r\nI get the same error if I try to install the built library into a 3.8 virtualenv, but with a 3.9 environment it works fine.\r\n\r\nIn order to successfully install arrow for Python 3.8 you'd probably also have to compile the the C++ libraries yourself, using the `-DPython3_EXECUTABLE` flag to point to the right Python.",
